# Stripped-down sshd config for integration tests. Substituted at
# runtime by `tests/common/ssh_fixture.rs`. The defaults here aim for:
#   * loopback-only listener (never expose an open port to a CI runner's
#     subnet),
#   * publickey-only auth against the committed fixture key,
#   * no PAM / GSSAPI / host-based fallback so the listener boots fast and
#     reproducibly on minimal CI images.
#
# Tokens substituted at fixture-spawn time:
#   __PORT__       random ephemeral port
#   __HOST_KEY__   absolute path to tests/fixtures/ssh/test_host_key
#   __AUTHKEYS__   absolute path to tests/fixtures/ssh/authorized_keys
#   __PIDFILE__    tmpdir path for sshd's pidfile

Port __PORT__
ListenAddress 127.0.0.1
HostKey __HOST_KEY__
AuthorizedKeysFile __AUTHKEYS__
PubkeyAuthentication yes
PasswordAuthentication no
KbdInteractiveAuthentication no
ChallengeResponseAuthentication no
UsePAM no
GSSAPIAuthentication no
HostbasedAuthentication no
PermitRootLogin prohibit-password
StrictModes no
PrintMotd no
LogLevel ERROR
PidFile __PIDFILE__
Subsystem sftp internal-sftp
